    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-03-24T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-03-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="606"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d606">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/1012.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Mexican Ambassador</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-03-24">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 24, 1911</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: With reference to the Department’s reply
                    of yesterday to your excellency’s communication of the 20th instant inquiring as
                    to Gen. Luque’s desire to purchase certain supplies on this side of the
                    frontier, and with reference also to the duties of American customs officials in
                    connection with such a transaction, I have the honor to point out to your
                    excellency that such officials could be concerned in the ordinary course of
                    their duties only with the proper enforcement of existing regulations, whereby
                    exports and imports may only be effected at an established port of entry.</p>
                <p>Accept, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Huntington Wilson.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
